J.M., a Child, Appellant,
v.
STATE of Florida, Appellee. Case No. 5D18-2849 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Fifth District. Opinion filed February 8, 2019 James S. Purdy, Public Defender, and Allison A. Havens, Assistant Public Defender, Daytona Beach, for Appellant. Ashley Moody, Attorney General, Tallahassee, and Pamela J. Koller, Assistant Attorney General, Daytona Beach, for Appellee. ON CONCESSION OF ERROR PER CURIAM.

Based on the State's concession of error, we reverse and remand for a reduction of J.M.'s conviction from a first-degree to a second-degree misdemeanor. See B.J.M. v. State , 185 So.3d 692 , 694 (Fla. 5th DCA 2016).

REVERSED AND REMANDED, with Instructions.

WALLIS, EISNAUGLE, and HARRIS, JJ., concur.
